Airbnb
Airbnb helps you find a place to crash, whether it’s a simple room in someone’s home or a luxurious beachfront property. The site also offers other kinds of bookings for travelers, such as tours, classes, and workshops. Whether you use Airbnb to find a place to sleep or for inspiration about what to do on your next trip, you’re guaranteed to see big, beautiful photographs of it all. Plan Harmony
The plan harmony is a reminder that gives you a recommended place for you and your group of friends. It has a calendar where anyone can add an event or an idea to this calendar. However, plan harmony also gives the assurance of viewing where you want to go, images, and what is available to eat, for a friends reunion, or a get together between colleagues.
There are various categories on the app or website, and each category has different prompts for the details you add to the event, such as flight number, car type or confirmation code, locations and links, and so on.
Cost tracking is a major part of group travel, and Plan Harmony seeks to make it easier by letting you add costs for each event and specifying whether it’s the group cost that’s to be evenly split or the per-person cost. Culture Trip
Culture Trip was once an app and site for reading about travel destinations, but it has expanded to now offer package tours. Search for the country or region you want to explore, and Culture Trip dishes up multi day trips to your destination of choice, like an eight-day trekking adventure through Patagonia or a safari through the busy streets of lagos. You book these packaged tours directly through the app or website.
Culture Trip also has plenty of advantages and is cost effective if you are planning to go in groups. You can also download the app on your phone’s play store or access it on the website.